OL,4,CLancastria: Service for Britain's worst
OL,5,Cmaritime disaster
OL,6, Commemorations to mark Britain's worst
OL,7, maritime disaster - the sinking of the
OL,8, Lancastria - have been held.
OL,10,FIt is estimated between 4,000 and 6,000
OL,11,Fpeople died when the ship was bombed by
OL,12,Fa Nazi plane on 17 June 1940.
OL,14,FPrime Minister Winston Churchill
OL,15,Fimposed a media blackout, fearing the
OL,16,Fdisaster's impact on morale during
OL,17,FWorld War Two.
OL,19,FDaniel Foster, a descendant of one of
OL,20,Fthe survivors, said: "It now falls upon
OL,21,Fthe families to carry on the story."
